Five people were arraigned at the Meru High court over the killing of a pastor at Mitunguu shopping
center, Imenti South constituency. Judge Francis Gikonyo ordered that Duncan Kiunga, Nahashon Kiogora, Felix
Karani, John Gituma, and Kiambi Mwaja be taken for mental tests before they can take plea. The lot is accused of raping and killing Roselyne Munala of the Redeemed Gospel Church on June 23, 2018. They are alleged to have dragged the pastor into a thicket, hit her with a blunt object in the
head and raped her. The five are also accused of stealing the pastor's mobile phone valued at Sh8,000. Munala's family learnt that she was missing after she failed to
return home on the fateful night. Prosecutor
Patrick Mitine said the accused will be taken for mental examination at Meru
Level Five Hospital. The case will be mentioned on August 8, 2018. Click here for the latest political news 